  "texts": [
    "Next, we average and merge the y-axis of the matrix, and the merged value c(edu i, edu j, r k) is called the importance index of edu i with relation r k.",
    "The RST distribution is then obtained by combining all c(edu i, edu j, r k).",
    "Based on this, we propose four fine-grained RST matrix distributions:",
    "• RST b wo: A binary, label-agnostic representation collapsing probabilities into a simple 1-or-0 regarding discourse connections.",
    "• RST b w: An extension of the binary distribution that includes relation labels, enriching the binary decisions with relational types."
  ],
